main event: A young civilian reported seeing a silver-colored, round or oval-shaped object over Quarryville, Pennsylvania on February 9, 1953.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 2-3 feet in diameter,The object resembled a typical US military training aircraft,No sound or lights were observed coming from the object,The conclusion of the report was undetermined due to limited information,The sighting occurred on the evening of February 9, 1953.
witness description: a young civilian aged 13 to 16 years old
